org.jamesframework.core.search.neigh.subset

Interface SubsetMove

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Move<SubsetSolution>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdditionMove, DeletionMove, SwapMove

    public interface SubsetMove
extends Move<SubsetSolution>
    General interface of a subset move that adds a number of IDs to the selection and/or removes a number of IDs. Extends the global interface Move, setting the solution type to SubsetSolution.
    Author:
    Herman De Beukelaer

    • Method Summary

      Methods

      Get the set of IDs that are removed from the selection by applying this move to a subset solution.
      int getNumAdded()
      Returns the number of added IDs, possibly 0.
